results.name: Smallest order m>0 for which there are n nonisomorphic finite groups of order m, or 0 if no such order exists.
comment: R. Keith Dennis conjectures that there are no 0's in this sequence. See A053403 for details.
In (John H. Conway, Heiko Dietrich and E. A. O'Brien, 2008), m is called the "minimal order attaining n" and is denoted by moa(n). - _Daniel Forgues_, Feb 15 2017
reference: J. H. Conway et al., The Symmetries of Things, Peters, 2008, p. 209.
